They need to find old restaurants around Seoul and deduct as many years as possible from the sum of their age in order to win. Stay tuned to find out which team wins!

530.TitleEnglish: Finding for Old Shops in Seoul: Old Shops Record (2)// Higher Club VS Lower Club: Highly Admired Recruitment! Penthouse (1)
530.SummaryEnglish: This week, Running Man continues with the Old Restaurant Race. The years have added up, but ironically, the oldest team member gets an unexpected gift from a rival sympathetic member turning the race into their favor. Next, Running Man welcomes guests Kim So Yeon, Lee Ji Ah, Eugene, and Ha Do Kwon from the show The Penthouse, while Kwang Soo and Ji Hyo serve out their penalty from the Jeju Island Special. They fight once again to gain their way into the penthouse.

531.SummaryEnglish: This week, the race from last week continues. The guests and members are divided into top class and bottom class where they receive money according to their mission results. Although they’re divided into two classes, it’s an individual race, so they keep an eye on each other to avoid getting betrayed. Who will make it to the penthouse? Stay tuned to find out!

532.TitleEnglish: Best Friend Special Friendship Race: The 1st Friendship Awards
532.SummaryEnglish: This week, Running Man gets ready for the year-end awards ceremony and kick-off today with their Friendship Award race. Each member gets assigned a best friend, and their chemistry will determine who goes home with a prize and who faces the penalty. Guests Cha Tae Hyun, Lee Mi Joo, Yang Dong Geun, Jang Dong Min, Huening Kai, and Choi Yeon Jun join the show as best friends.

533.SummaryEnglish: This week, Lee Si Young, Lee Do Hyun, Song Kang, and Lee Jin Wook, the four leads of the drama “Sweet Home,” join the members for a race called ‘The Apartment You Live In.’ In the race, they have to find a monster hidden among the residents of the Running Apartment in order to avoid getting the penalty. Will they be able to find the monster?

534.TitleEnglish: Ryu Hyun-jin X Kim Kwang-hyun: Sparkling Stove League
534.SummaryEnglish: This week, the Major League Baseball players Ryu Hyun Jin and Kim Kwang Hyun join 2021 Running League Rookie Draft where team owners Yu Jae Seok and Yang Se Chan pick rookie players for their teams. In order to win the race, they need to win each mission and earn as much money as possible. The player and team owner with the least amount of money gets a penalty.

535.TitleEnglish: New Year Blues Race: 2020 Year-end Closing
535.SummaryEnglish: This week, the members are joined by the four leads of the upcoming movie, “New Year Blues,” Yoo Yeon Seok, Lee Yeon Hee, Choi Soo Young, and Yoo Teo. Since it’s the last episode of 2020, the guests and the members participate in missions where they send off the old year and welcome the upcoming year. Which team will win and which team will get the penalty?

536.TitleEnglish: 2021 Card Shark Association New Year's Party: The Return of Gamblers (1)
536.SummaryEnglish: This week, the Card Shark Association is back to kick off the new year with a party. The fierce competition over caramels gets heated as the association’s chairperson position hangs in the balance. Will Jae Seok keep his seat as the chairman and serve two consecutive terms? Or will the association bring in the new year with a new chairperson? Stay tuned to find out.

537.TitleEnglish: 2021 Card Shark Association New Year's Party: The Return of Gamblers (2)// Planning Intention Race: The Rewriting Running Man (1)
537.SummaryEnglish: The Card Shark Association New Year's Party comes to an end. The last mission is a cutthroat game that will determine who gets to go home first. Meanwhile, the members regroup after a week. A new race to decide whose idea will be used to update the outdated Running Man website begins. Stay tuned to see who has the catchiest and funniest ideas for the website.

538.TitleEnglish: Planning Intention Race: The Rewriting Running Man (2)
538.SummaryEnglish: The new race leading up to the long-awaited update of the Running Man website is now in full swing. The members present each of their ideas for the production objective and member introductions. After that, they must play games to add their names to the roulette which will decide the final winner. Stay tuned to see whose idea made it onto the website after all.

539.TitleEnglish: Race for the Club Activity Money, The Burning 18 Again
539.SummaryEnglish: In this week’s episode, the Running Man members are joined by two guests, Kim Bo Sung and Defconn. They go back to high school where they are divided into three clubs. The band club, dance club, and student guidance club must compete against one another in various classes to win the scholarship. Stay tuned to see who wins!

540.TitleEnglish: Uneasy Sisters: My Little Old Brother
540.SummaryEnglish: This week, three charismatic actresses join the Running Man members to divide into three groups of siblings. Each family must compete for an allowance which the big sister distributes to the younger siblings. However, the final penalty is decided by how much money each individual has, leading to a game of wits even within the family. Stay tuned to see who must carry out the penalty.

541.TitleEnglish: 2021 New Year Driving Out Bad Luck Race: Take My Bad Luck Away
541.SummaryEnglish: This week, three young actors visit Running Man for a race to drive out bad luck in the new year. The Running Man members and their guests divide into three teams and play a series of games to see which team ends up with the least number of Penalty Men. The final penalty is a giant water bomb that will surely wash away all of their bad luck. Stay tuned to see who gets soaked!

542.TitleEnglish: 2021 Running Man Neighborhood Athletic Meet with "The Penthouse"
542.SummaryEnglish: For the last day of the Lunar New Year holidays, the three actors of The Penthouse, Park Eun Seok, Yoon Jong Hun, and Ha Do Kwon, visit Running Man. They join the show for 2021 Running Man Neighborhood Athletic Meet where they compete to gather more trophy stamps in their stamp books. Stay tuned to see what kind of funny penalty the staff has come up with!

543.TitleEnglish: Running Man Investment Contest: Genius Investors Race
543.SummaryEnglish: The Running Man members enter into an investment contest. They begin with 500 dollars of R money each and enter the stock market of 2011. As they progress toward the year 2020, which is the year that the contest will end, the members with varying degrees of experience in stocks are tempted by all kinds of information. Stay tuned to find out who ends up earning the most R money.

544.TitleEnglish: Running Man Investment Contest: Genius Investors Race/Suk-jin's Day: Cash to See You
544.SummaryEnglish: The Running Man Investment Contest goes on with Se Chan in the lead. As the members make their investments based on the information they gather and their instincts, it becomes a matter of who will be in last place. After the Investment Contest, the Running Man members get together to celebrate Seok Jin’s birthday and begin a new race.

545.TitleEnglish: It's Time to Find the Gold Race
545.SummaryEnglish: Continuing from last week’s episode, everyone gathers to celebrate Seok Jin’s birthday. They get a letter saying that there is gold hidden somewhere in Running Village. Seok Jin gets to choose two members to join his team and the others compete as individual players. The winners get to choose two people who will get the penalty. Stay tuned to see who they are!

546.TitleEnglish: Running Dynasty Records: The Appearance of The Evil Spirit
546.SummaryEnglish: In this week’s episode, the four actors of the new drama “Joseon Exorcist” join the Running Man members for the Running Dynasty Records Race. There are two evil spirits who hide among the humans. They are divided into one king and three teams of nobles, eunuchs, and slaves. They must find who the evil spirits are in order to defeat them. Stay tuned to see if they succeed!

547.TitleEnglish: The Dignity of the Grand Award Race
547.SummaryEnglish: Two of the Running Man members, Jae Seok and Jong Kook, are Grand Award winners in the end-of-year entertainment awards. The members divide into Team Yu Grand Award and Team Kim Grand Award and compete for points. Only the winner gets to be exempt from the penalty. Who will be the three unlucky members to get the penalty?

548.TitleEnglish: Catch the Stars Among Free Agents, Stars' Contract War Race
548.SummaryEnglish: This week, four of the Running Man members become CEOs of new entertainment agencies. First, they must sign contracts with the artists they want to work with. With Jessi and Jang Woo Young joining the contract war, things get quite competitive. This time, two CEOs and two artists will get the penalty. Stay tuned to find out who they are.

549.TitleEnglish: A Day of Brave Idol Stars Race
549.SummaryEnglish: In this week’s episode, the girl group that is taking music charts by storm, Brave Girls joins Running Man for A Day of Brave Idol Stars Race. They divide into three teams and compete to see who can be the best idol star. With various crew members joining in as judges for the missions, the results are as unpredictable as ever. Stay tuned to find out who gets the penalty!

550.TitleEnglish: Sweet and Scary Way Home Race
550.SummaryEnglish: In this week’s episode, Cho Sae Ho and Cho A join in on The Sweet and Scary Way Home Race. They divide into two teams, Team Gangnam and Team Mapo. The teams compete to determine where they will shoot the ending scene. Which team will get to have an easy trip home after a long day of work? Stay tuned to find out!

551.TitleEnglish: I Also Want to Find an Entertainment Partner (1)
551.SummaryEnglish: This week, the Running Man members and three beautiful actresses head to Variety Village. There, they have a race to find the perfect variety show partner. Each person must do well in the games and charm the contenders of the opposite sex to gain points. The person with the least number of points faces a very harsh penalty. Stay tuned to see who finds their perfect partner.

552.TitleEnglish: I Also Want to Find an Entertainment Partner (2)// The Entering Class of 1991 Is Back (1)
552.SummaryEnglish: The Perfect Partner Signal, Variety Village Race continues and the 11 entertainers try to find their perfect variety show partner. As the people who are left without a partner face the penalty, everyone tries their best to find a match. Meanwhile, a new race begins with the theme of going back to 1991. Stay tuned and watch the Running Man members show off their retro vibes.

553.TitleEnglish: The Entering Class of 1991 Is Back (2)
553.SummaryEnglish: The Running Man members continue with the “Entering Class of 1991 Is Back” race this week. The members take a trip down memory lane and go back to enjoying the music, food, and games of the 1990s. They compete to win nostalgic items as presents to avoid the cringe-worthy penalty. Stay tuned to see who gets the penalty at the end!

554.TitleEnglish: When You Go to the TV Station Race
554.SummaryEnglish: This week, the Running Man members go to the SBS building for the Credit Card Payment, When You Go to the TV Station Race. They compete in games that are in the theme of SBS variety shows. They try to win the right to decide whose credit card to use to pay for their activities. Stay tuned to see who gets the humiliating penalty at the end.

555.TitleEnglish: Smart Escape Race, Empty Head Land
555.SummaryEnglish: This week, the Running Man members head to Empty Head Land for the Smart Escape Race. They must solve quizzes and play games to find a way to escape from Empty Head Land. With many twists and turns, the race is more exciting than ever. Stay tuned to see who must carry out the penalty and be called dunce for good.

556.SummaryEnglish: Sung Si Kyung and Lee Yong Jin join Running Man this week as the CEOs of two competing matchmaking companies. The male members join the two CEOs as their employees to search for their clients’ ideal types. So Min and Ji Hyo are the clients who get to decide which company did a better job at finding their ideal partners. Stay tuned to see which team wins!

557.TitleEnglish: Going Home Race, Read the Room
557.SummaryEnglish: In this week’s episode, the Running Man members compete against each other to see who can go home the fastest. However, the Read the Room Race isn’t as simple as it seems. With hidden missions that allow the members to earn R coins, they must figure out how they can win the most coins. Stay tuned to see the hidden secret behind this race!

558.TitleEnglish: Three Meals for Jae Seok Race
558.SummaryEnglish: This week’s episode is based on an idea that Jae Seok jokingly mentioned last week, where he dresses up as Lord Yu, the nobleman, and the others make him three meals for the day. They can earn or find coins to buy penalty sticks for other members, and they can even pay to have the lord replaced. Stay tuned to see who wins the prize and who gets the penalty!

559.SummaryEnglish: This week is Kwang Soo’s last episode on Running Man. The members get together for a special send-off race, where they must help Kwang Soo work off his amazingly large prison sentence for all the mischief he caused over the past 11 years. Stay tuned to see the tearful goodbyes and what kind of secret missions the members carried out.

560.SummaryEnglish: The seven members of the famous Running Game Club have their first get-together. They compete in various games to win points in order to avoid the mystery penalty at the end. As the members try to outsmart and connive their ways to victory, some members seem to have better luck than others. Stay tuned to see which two members face off for the penalty!

561.SummaryEnglish: Today, the team assembles to enjoy their summer vacation. As they all talk about each other’s new summer outfits, today’s guests appear and join them. To make the vacation more interesting, they get a chance to earn over a thousand dollars. Defeat others, complete missions, win votes, and trust no one. Stay tuned to find out the winner of the prize money!

562.TitleEnglish: Talk Nightmare, The Day of Chattering Race
562.SummaryEnglish: In Korea, chattering with your friends and families is often expressed with the word “dried pollack”. And for today’s mission, the members are to continue talking before the 10-second silence fills the air. Unless they successfully deduct the total count of dried pollacks, a selected few will inevitably have to go through one of many troublesome penalties. Whatever the case may be, Jae Seok who loves talking starts the nonstop conversation with the beloved members.

563.SummaryEnglish: It’s been 11 years since the first episode of Running Man, and the penalty continues to threaten the members. In today’s episode, the members are divided into three groups and will compete for one of the seven roles in a family photo. Knowing that some roles might be tedious and humiliating, members do not hesitate to deceive one another. Even Ji Hyo, who’s been honest and straightforward, decides to act for her own good this time. Stay tuned!

564.TitleEnglish: Make Your Wish Come True & Pay The Price Later Race
564.SummaryEnglish: The actors and actresses from “The Witch’s Diner” team participate in today’s race, and the winners will have their wishes granted. Among them is Ha Do Kwon who can’t seem to accept the consecutive defeats against Jong Kook. Ji Hyo, one of the original members of Running Man, also joins as a guest, but the other members find it hard to treat her like one. With Nam Ji Hyun’s disarming smile getting her team the upper hand, the race tightens.

565.SummaryEnglish: The fees collected for the Comedian Association have been stolen by the prime suspect, a person whom members are very close to. And now it’s the responsibility of the remaining members to make up for the missing amount. The members are divided into groups according to their seniority as Lee Yong Jin, today’s special guest and Se Chan’s colleague, joins the race. To avoid the penalty and make up for the missing amount, the members must clear the missions.

566.TitleEnglish: Choose The Fate From Your Own Hands: The First Filial Piety Shooting Operation
566.SummaryEnglish: The staff decides to give the members a chance to earn cash according to their own choices so that they can spend time with their parents. However, the cash prizes also come at the risk of losing cash. The members can either choose the safe option to earn a moderate amount, or they can choose a riskier option for higher compensation that also has a chance of losing cash. As the race progresses, more complicated options are revealed to the members.

567.TitleEnglish: Team Choosing Race: Young-ji VS Young-ji
567.SummaryEnglish: In today’s episode, rapper Lee Young Ji and Hur Young Ji of KARA join other members in a race to lead their team to victory. With each Young Ji being the team leader, two teams make their utmost efforts to win each mission. However, the points are given to the team leaders first before they are distributed to the members, and this is where the members start to bear a grudge against their team leaders. Stay tuned!

568.TitleEnglish: Find The Best Price Doll: Strict Doll Appraiser
568.SummaryEnglish: In today’s episode, each member gets to choose one of Artist Kim So Hee’s handmade dolls at her Doll Exhibition. Suddenly, Ms. Kim collapses and dies mysteriously after looking at one of the dolls they’re holding. Who will find the most expensive doll to inherit her prized dolls and assets? Stay tuned to find out!

569.TitleEnglish: Couple Race, You Raise a Man Up
569.SummaryEnglish: In today’s episode, Yoon Si Yoon, Park Ki Woong, and Ahn Hee Yeon join the show to compete in the You Raise a Man Up Race. With Jong Kook’s being the strongest of them all, the members and even the guests try to put a stop to his winning streak. Just when everyone thought it would be impossible to tame Jong Kook and his wildness, one of the guests manages to drag him down.

570.TitleEnglish: Catch the Mafia, Running Man in Chaos
570.SummaryEnglish: It’s been years since the members raced alongside each other, but some still don’t have enough trust in others when it comes to Mafia Game. This time, the members not only have to stay incognito but also have to complete the given mission. As the race starts, everyone avoids Jong Kook’s keen eyes in order to hide their true identity. However, some start to suspect Jong Kook of being the Mafia.

571.TitleEnglish: Gym Revival Project, Trainer Jong Kook and National Team
571.SummaryEnglish: Trainer Kook, one of the celebrities who enjoy working out, finds his gym on the verge of going bankrupt. In order to recover from the difficult situation, he invites other members to join him at the gym. As expected, none of the members are serious about the gym or the workout, and even Jong Kook finds it difficult to keep them under control.

572.TitleEnglish: Female Volleyball Team, Fierce Transfer Contract
572.SummaryEnglish: The members of the women’s national volleyball team join the show to compete against the Running Man members at the 2022 Running Man League Draft. Especially, there is someone on the national team who looks and behaves exactly like Kwang Soo. Meanwhile, Jong Kook doesn’t seem as bossy as before now that he’s with the players of the national volleyball team.

573.TitleEnglish: Fierce Transfer Race 2: Negotiation of Long Legs
573.SummaryEnglish: The members of the women’s national volleyball team continue to demand more salary and welfare packages from their trainers even though they’ve failed to perform well in the foot volleyball games. Meanwhile, whenever the members look at or listen to Yeon Koung, they cannot shake off the feeling that their old friend is back.

574.TitleEnglish: To Become Italian Gentlemen, Elegant Road of Western Dishes
574.SummaryEnglish: It’s finally the last round of the Fierce Transfer Race. This time, the players are given a huge volleyball to compete against the opponent team on a court prepared in a swimming pool. Meanwhile, the Running Man members hold a special event to test each other’s guts whether they can admit to something they would want to hide for the rest of their lives.

575.SummaryEnglish: The members are invited to play in the Webfoot Octopus Game, and they must decide whether they will participate in this high-stake game with 3,000 dollars of prize money. While some struggle to survive on their own, others work in groups to eliminate others. Who’s going to be the final survivor? Stay tuned to find out.

576.SummaryEnglish: The members welcome Yeji, Luda, BIBI, and MC Minzy to the show, and they prepare to compete in the Golden Ratio Race. The race will consist of many games, and the last one seems a bit tricky. As seen in “Squid Game”, two teams must walk across a bridge of either wooden floors or Styrofoam floors. However, Ji Hyo seems to be pretty good at the game and surprises others. Stay tuned!

577.SummaryEnglish: Joon Ho invites the members to his huge mansion to have the Mansion of Misfortune Race and gain good energy from Running Man team. They start the race with a bag of chocolates, and the winner will be decided by the number of chocolates they gain from each race. Will he be able to win the race and become the icon of promise? Stay tuned to find out!

578.TitleEnglish: My Money Naesan Running Mountaineering Association
578.SummaryEnglish: Jang Hyuk, today’s special guest, joins the members for My Alpine Club Race. They are informed that they will be going on hiking, and as expected, Seok Jin doesn’t fail to disappoint the crew with his weird fashion. Meanwhile, the members are told that they will have to pay for their own expenses except for the chosen few. The struggle to become the minority begins.

579.SummaryEnglish: As the heroines of “Street Woman Fighter”, the four leaders including Honey J, Aiki, Lee Jung, and Monika visit the show for another round of competition. With selected Running Man members next to each leader, the race begins. Although they might look happy-go-lucky on the outside, the tension continues to build up as the race proceeds. Stay tuned!

580.SummaryEnglish: The time has finally come, and the members accept the challenge from the production crew. Both parties will undergo a series of games in order to see the opponent suffer from a penalty. In negotiations, one doesn’t always get what they want, but one gets what one manages to negotiate. The production crew wants to see every single Running Man suffer, but will they be able to beat the members in the game? Stay tuned to find out!

581.SummaryEnglish: A long time ago, Nostradamus, a reputed seer, once predicted that the world will end in 1999. With only a few days left of the year 1999, the members gather to fight against the resistance, Nostra and Damus. SAN of ATEEZ, Jin Ji Hee, and Arin of OH MY GIRL will support the members, but no one knows exactly who the resistance is. They will just have to find out. Stay tuned!

582.TitleEnglish: Yang Se Chan the Good Son
582.SummaryEnglish: Se Chan's birthday is coming up, and his variety show parents are here to throw him a fancy birthday party. He wants to become a perfect son for his variety show parents by treating them with allowance. However, they do not even hesitate to stab him in the back, as they are blinded by the money and prize they will get from the race. Stay tuned to find out who wins the race!

583.SummaryEnglish: Seok Jin is well known for his gullible personality. In today’s episode, the members become his cells and help him make the right choice during his busy schedule as a superstar. His cells need to persuade him to choose their suggestion and earn Gullible Coins to win the race. Let’s find out how Seok Jin will survive today with his adorable cells!

584.SummaryEnglish: The members are ready to celebrate the year-end party with Chung Hwa, Do Kwon, and Young Ji, who brought great honor to Running Man this year. They prepare special performances and even cook for the party dishes on their own. However, they only have limited amounts of ingredients, and a war begins to steal them from each other. Will they be able to enjoy a peaceful year-end party?

585.SummaryEnglish: Team Jong Kook and Team Jae Seok have to cook three dishes with the eggs they have stolen from each other. They have to finish the cooking mission no matter what to win the race. Meanwhile, we have the behind-the-scenes of the members at the Entertainment Awards, and to celebrate the year 2022, they have their fortune read as well.

586.SummaryEnglish: With So Min’s talents in fortune-telling, she organizes a consultation to see what lies ahead of each member in 2022. However, it turns out the consultation isn’t free. The members now have to play and win games in order to get discounts on their fees. So Min even endures one of the worst nightmares that can happen to a Running Man member. Stay tuned and find out if they manage to pay all the amounts due.

587.TitleEnglish: The Seniority War of the Youngest Members
587.SummaryEnglish: The seniority war of the youngest members begins between Se Chan and So Min, and the members and the production crews choose who's last in the hierarchy. The rest of the members buy ballots with the coins they gain from playing games and pick a member who will be the last one in everything. Who will be the youngest member in 2022?

588.SummaryEnglish: In this week's episode, the members are all dressed up in trendy outfits to welcome the most iconic fashion models to Running Man. The members and the guests are sorted into teams according to their height, and the race is about earning points to gain either shoe lifts or blocks to climb up higher than other teams.

589.TitleEnglish: The Modeling World: Part II & The Myth of Dangun in the Year of the Black Tiger
589.SummaryEnglish: In this week's episode, the members and the guests continue with the Frightening Quiz to purchase more blocks and shoe lifts. Finally, the last game is the Acorn War, in which they need to collect enough acorns to get elimination tickets to play our all-time favorite, Name Tag Elimination. Who will become the tallest among them?

590.TitleEnglish: The Myth of Dangun in the Year of the Black Tiger, Part 2
590.SummaryEnglish: To celebrate the Year of the Tiger, Running Man invited Eunhyuk, Seul Ki, and Soo Ah, who were born in 1986, to have The Myth of Dangun in the Year of the Black Tiger Race. Se Chan and So Min, who were born in the same year, will be tigers with the guests, and the rest of the members will be the bears in the race. However, there are two poachers hiding among them and stealing their garlic cloves. Who are the poachers in disguise?

591.SummaryEnglish: In this week’s episode, Pak Se Ri is here as a coach of a variety show to complete the race with the members. All five members are subject to a penalty but, Se Ri will lead them throughout the 18 mission holes, to get the prize money. They can buy penalty exemption cards and even reveal the hidden option with the money they earn. Will they all be able to get away from the penalty this week?

592.TitleEnglish: Card Shark Association: Those Who Read Card Sharks' Minds
592.SummaryEnglish: After a year, the members of the Card Shark Association reunited with the new leader, Chairperson Ha. This time, they brought Pushover Joo to join their games so they could extort all of his assets with their skills. However, anyone can become a winner or a pushover in the world of variety shows. Who will win this round and make a fortune?

593.SummaryEnglish: Seok Jin’s favorite people are here to join the race this week to back him up in his special episode. They introduce their new song to the members for the first time, and they show perfect harmony as a vocal group. However, will they be able to maintain the team spirit throughout the race?

594.SummaryEnglish: In this week’s episode, the members are going to choose the captain of Running Man. The winner of the election will lead the team for the next month and get various benefits during his or her term. When they are about to fight with one another for the position, a special candidate joins them in the election even though he is not a member of Running Man. Who will be able to win this glorious title?

595.TitleEnglish: This Is My First Time Being a Captain
595.SummaryEnglish: In this week’s episode, Ji Hee and Jun Hwan reunite for the first time in 11 years on Running Man. Even before they catch up with each other, they have to lead their old-school and yet childish members as the captains to win the race. They also get to distribute the prize money to their team members after each game. Will they be able to handle the members of Running Man?

596.TitleEnglish: This Is My First Time Being a Captain (Part 2) & BTOB without BTOB Special
596.SummaryEnglish: In this week’s episode, Ji Hee and Jun Hwan continue to lead their teams for the final race, Who Rang the Bell. They take turns to play Team Defense and Team Offense to win the points. Meanwhile, since BTOB cannot join us for their special episode, the members are divided into two teams according to their blood type for the BTOB race. Which team will receive the penalty at the end of the race?

597.SummaryEnglish: In this week’s episode, the war of love begins in Running Man with three beautiful actresses joining the race. The male members pick one female member to give candy, and they can exchange them with ballots for the male member's popularity poll. Who will be the favored winners to get the most candies and votes?

598.SummaryEnglish: In this week's episode, the members will take a break from games and go on a trip together as Captain Jee suggested. Therefore, they get to hang out and have fun with no missions and penalties as well. However, one of the members finds a key and a mysterious box with a warning on it. What will be the secret of today’s race?

599.TitleEnglish: How Much Do You Want to Spend?
599.SummaryEnglish: In this week’s episode, the members go around different shops and stores to spend money. However, they only have to use the debit cards they randomly chose at the beginning of the race. Therefore, they have to figure out the amount in their cards to avoid going bankrupt. Who will be the one to go broke and receive the penalty?

600.SummaryEnglish: In this week’s episode, the members celebrate the 600th episode by carrying out their missions with the viewers. The race will have Part One and Part Two, and the missions for this race are based on the viewers’ recommendations through social media. Every time they complete a mission as a group, they will save money for charities!

601.SummaryEnglish: In this week’s episodes, the members and the guests participate in a race that brings back childhood memories. They are divided into three teams, and the first team to win in each game gets to choose seven pieces of bread that contain Runningmon stickers. They need to find as many stickers as possible to complete the Runningdex. Who will be the first team to complete it?

602.SummaryEnglish: In this week’s episodes, Town A and Town B will compete, and Chief Kook can choose the town to join in every mission through negotiation with both towns. The winning team members and the losing team members get different amounts of money. At the end of the race, the top two with the largest amount of money win and get a prize, and the bottom two get a penalty. Which town will be able to take their revenge?

603.SummaryEnglish: The members are called upon one by one to hear the rules for a new game. But some are not able to pay attention properly due to a disturbance. As the game starts, the staff crew place bets on those who they think will win. The members must now do their best to win each match. The winner will receive a great prize along with their thankful supporters. Stay tuned to check out the winning party!

604.TitleEnglish: User's Guide to Black and White Roses
604.SummaryEnglish: The handsome idol stars, ASTRO visit Running Man. The person who is happiest about their appearance is So Min. With So Min, ASTRO must compete against team Running Man and obtain roses from So Min to get the winning prize. Running Man members must also obtain roses from Ji Hyo to get a chance for the prize as well. Tune in to see who gets the most roses and wins the luxurious grand prize!

605.SummaryEnglish: The heroines of the movie 2037 have come to clear their names as they become the suspects in the elimination of Running Man’s youngest producer. The inmates must go through missions and search the whole English Village to find clues that lead to the true culprit. Although So Min is one of the movie casts, she does not have time to promote the film as she needs to clear her name first.

606.TitleEnglish: Investing Geniuses Go to NY, Part 1
606.SummaryEnglish: The Running Man members are getting ready to make some money through investment in the year 2022. But this time, instead of Korean stocks, they will be dealing with American stocks in Wall Street. In order to be ready for the huge project, they go through quizzes and missions to enhance their knowledge. Tune in to see how the elite brains of Running Man make smart investments!

607.TitleEnglish: Investing Geniuses Go to NY, Part 2
607.SummaryEnglish: The Running Man members compete with each other in a race in which they must earn money through investment. By listening to English information, they invest money in stocks every year hoping for a jackpot. Investing up until the year 2022, the best investors will be getting a great American prize while the worst investor must go through a harsh penalty. Stay tuned for the Genius Investors!

608.SummaryEnglish: In some companies, allowing employees to have flexible working hours is becoming a trend. To follow the trend, Running Man sets on a race to who gets off work faster. The members go through games and missions to finish today’s schedule as quickly as possible. The lucky ones may go home extremely early, and the unlucky might have to stay overtime.

609.SummaryEnglish: Summer is now officially here. Since the members cannot go on a vacation because of work, the staff and the viewer comments help them enjoy themselves on today’s show. With gaming skills and a little bit of luck, the members get to choose what kind of activities to do. If successful, they get to do whatever they want. If not, they must do what the staff has in store for them.

610.SummaryEnglish: The whole team is invited to Jong Kook’s place. The members are to control their stress level while playing games to earn money and not be selected for the final penalty. However, it is not easy for them to control their stress due to Jong Kook’s never-ending nitpicking. Tune in to find out who would not be able to withstand the stress caused at Jong Kook’s house!

611.SummaryEnglish: The members of Running Man are up for a nice meal on today’s race. However, as it always has been, they must earn the food. Divided into two teams, the race for treats begins. With Yoon Bo Mi, Park Cho Rong, Mirani, and KCM as guests, the teams go through challenges that test their knowledge and emotional endurance. Stay tuned to see which team gets the final penalty!

612.SummaryEnglish: The improvisation skills of the members are challenged today. They compete by improvising in given situations to win Running Coins. Although everyone must face a certain penalty in the end, the ones who finish with higher ranks get to choose their penalty from the penalty list. Tune in to see who wins the most coins to get the advantage.

613.SummaryEnglish: Today, the members travel through the Korean chronicles. With each game having a certain chronicle as its concept, they must figure out the corrupt official to win. The members must unite to complete missions and doubt each other at the same time. Tune in to learn about Korean chronicles and see if the corrupt officials can prevail.

614.SummaryEnglish: The Tag of Tails takes place. In order to become the head of the whole group, they must be both smart and fast. Strategy is essential and timing must be perfect. The members go through missions and find the name tag of others to make them their tails. No matter how well anyone plays, there will only be one head who prevails.

615.SummaryEnglish: The Tag of Tails ends with Se Chan as the winner. While Se Chan and Jae Seok have the most points, the next game begins. In the Race of Groups, Running Man has special guests who will become the captain of each team. The captains must guess who has the most money and recruit them into their team. The game of wits between the rich and poor begins!

616.SummaryEnglish: The three team leaders have chosen their teammates. With the money they receive from their teammates, the final games of the Race of Groups begin. The members must defeat other teams to obtain more money. In the end, they will be ranked individually depending on the amount of money they make.

617.SummaryEnglish: The members gather today upon a mini version of Korea. To avoid the penalty and win prizes, they must skillfully invest in imaginary land and earn money. Depending on the smart or bad choices they make, some may smile and some may cry. The characteristics of each land can either be used in a creative way to make money or might bring misfortune to the owner.

618.SummaryEnglish: The team is taken back to the Joseon dynasty. Wondering what today’s race is, they learn that they have to go up against ghosts. They must find their Books of Fate and earn coins to extend their lifespan. If they fail to do so, the Grim Reapers will appear to take away their lives and make them into ghosts.

619.SummaryEnglish: The members compete in games to avoid getting penalty stickers. Based on the ranks of each game, the members will be writing each other’s names on the slots of roulettes. Through games that need both physical strength and smart thinking, they must lower their chances of getting chosen by the roulette.

620.SummaryEnglish: Three strong actresses appear on today’s Running Man. Jin Seo Yeon, Ok Ja Yeon, and Choi Yeo Jin join to win the prize for the day. The members are divided into two teams, and they must correctly guess who has how many coins. The team that ends up with more coins will win the special prize that is prepared for the Chuseok Holiday.

621.TitleEnglish: We Want to Go to Gangwon
621.SummaryEnglish: Because of the harsh typhoon, the members are led to Gangwon as plans change last minute. There, they will be playing the final games that will determine who gets the Whatever Penalties. The members are divided into teams and compete in indoor games. Depending on which team loses, the star of the Whatever Penalty Project will be chosen.

622.SummaryEnglish: The time has come for the members to decide what penalty they must go through and who to receive it. But before they decide anything, they get a chance to cross out some penalty choices if they win games as a whole team. In the end, however, one more member to get the penalty with Se Chan will be chosen randomly.

623.SummaryEnglish: The members today go all the way to Cheorwon. Although the staff crew promises them a delightful trip, it doesn’t mean every member will be having it. By choosing either Go or Stop, each person will either enjoy a therapeutic event or a disastrous activity. With a little bit of luck and by making smart choices, their shoot today will be very different from one another.

624.TitleEnglish: Mr. Run, How's the Food Over There?
624.SummaryEnglish: The race of Go and Stop comes to an end. The lucky ones who make the right choice gets to go home. For the new race, the knowledge level of the members is tested. While having a spy among them, the team must work as one in answering quizzes to get hints of who the spy is. If they fail to guess who it is, everyone except the spy will be facing a penalty.

625.TitleEnglish: A Walk Around The Famous Neighborhood
625.SummaryEnglish: On a rainy day in Seoul, the crew tries to come up with an indoor activity. However, despite the rain, they choose to do a tour around Seoul. Just as always, the tour will not be ordinary. The members must finish the given mission before their pedometer numbers reach a certain amount. If they succeed, they get to go home early.

626.SummaryEnglish: Today’s guest is none other than the great boxer, Manny Pacquiao. He visits Korea for an event match with a Korean boxer, but also insists on visiting Running Man as well. With Manny, today’s race will be a competition between two teams. The members should win games to get as much money as possible to buy the penalty exemption card.

627.SummaryEnglish: Jin of BTS visits Running Man. As his real name is also Seok Jin, Jee Seok Jin and Kim Seok Jin go up against each other with their own teams. To receive fewer penalty balls, they must win games. However, the members can switch teams with an exchange ticket to join the winning team. To evade the final penalty, everyone must win games and be smart when using the tickets.

628.SummaryEnglish: The weather is getting chilly and fall has officially come. To celebrate the new season, the members dress in nice autumn clothing. However, today’s race does not allow all of them to wear proper clothing. Depending on how well the members play each game, some must wear summer or winter clothing throughout the day.

629.SummaryEnglish: The members greet three great actors as guests today. Kim Rae Won, Park Byung Eun, and Jeong Sang Hun join a race to find two spies. They are divided into three teams and must avoid having a spy on the team by switching teammates. Through quiz games and a Name Tag Elimination race, the team leaders can get hints on who might be the spies.

630.SummaryEnglish: Kim Ji Eun and Cho Sae Ho join as guests to participate in a brain-racking game of currencies. The members must choose teams wisely and win as many games as possible to get money. Depending on the result of each game, the price of the bills that everyone has will differ. In the end, a grand prize awaits the one who saves the most amount of money.

631.TitleEnglish: Will We Have Our First Win in the World Cup?
631.SummaryEnglish: The team gathers around to watch the FIFA World Cup Qatar 2022. Everyone cheers desperately as Korea goes up against Ghana. However, the result leaves everyone in disappointment. After the game, the members are divided into two teams. By choosing every decision based on a random number, they must arrive to the finishing location faster than the other team.

632.SummaryEnglish: The Lucky Number Race continues and Team Jae Seok is far behind Team Seok Jin. Team Jae Seok must move quicker to defeat Team Seok Jin. As both teams must perform a number of missions, Jae Seok still has a chance to turn the table around. But no matter who wins, a final additional game awaits the members with prizes.

633.SummaryEnglish: To celebrate the end of the year, the team holds a party with two stars. Singers BE’O and Jukjae visit as guests to participate in the Race of Stars. Divided into three teams, each team must compete to obtain Star Cards and Poop Cards to make a combination of Star-Poop-Star. Depending on the result of each game, some teams will enjoy the warm indoors while others must stay outside in the cold.

634.SummaryEnglish: Christmas has come and Running Man celebrates it to the fullest. The members are given 300 dollars each to buy things for themselves as presents. However, those will actually be for the citizens of Seoul. Santa Yu roams around Seoul with his Rudolphs to hand out gifts. But they are not for free. The citizens and the crew must work together and win games to receive the prizes.

635.SummaryEnglish: To celebrate the new year, the crew decides to gather and spend time together as a family. One of Running Man’s close friends, Joo Woo Jae also joins them. They gather at a small house in the countryside and prepare warm meals that will melt the cold. Although they go through troubles in the freezing weather, they withstand it together as one big happy family.

636.SummaryEnglish: The crew cooks dinner which also becomes fierce to prepare. After a hearty meal, Se Chan finally joins the family when everyone is resting inside. He is told that he must choose some members to prepare breakfast with. The next day, the challenge of making breakfast takes place and the staff announces who will win the golden rabbits.

637.SummaryEnglish: Choo Sung Hoon, Kim Dong Hyun, Jung Chan Sung, and Choi Doo Ho appear to make some fight money. The fighters must give a good performance in each game to negotiate a higher salary. Those who get the least amount of money at the end must face a penalty while the high rankers are gifted with prizes.

638.SummaryEnglish:
The chairman of Soonbak Group has passed. Among the Running Man heirs, a new chairman must be seated. However, the cast from Reborn Rich also joins the competition in getting the shares of the group. The children of the late chairman try to play smart in order to get the most shares. But no matter how smart they are, luck ultimately chooses the winner.

Guest: Kim Shin-rok

639.SummaryEnglish:
As today’s guests, all the members of IVE have come to compete. Everyone will be bunnies today and play games in different teams. However, a Rabbit with No Liver is among the teams as a spy, and today’s mission is to guess who it is. The Running Man crew are close enough to know who’s lying, but they cannot seem to figure out if any of the IVE members are lying.

Guest: IVE

640.SummaryEnglish:
Jang Hyuk and Donnie Yen visit Running Man to teach the members what true martial arts is. To do that, the two masters and the crew team up into two teams and compete in two games. Depending on the results, the person with the highest points gets to win special presents that Donnie has prepared himself.

Guests: Jang Hyuk and Donnie Yen

641.SummaryEnglish: All Running Man members are gathered to go on a retreat and will be spending time in each other’s company. The same daily routines seem much more enjoyable with their friends and colleagues by their sides. Parties and games are a must on retreats, and they are even better when penalty transfer cards are on the line. The conversations deepen until their last mission is revealed.

642.SummaryEnglish:
After listening to a heart touching performance by M.O.M, the members along with Heo Kyeong Hwan, Byul, and SEOGI are invited to a winter get-together on a field of ice where the staff members are preparing something weird for them. While Haha is having difficulties shooting Running Man with his wife, everyone is worried about Kyung Hwan because of his underperformance as a guest on the show. With all the worries behind, the race begins.

Guests: Byul, Heo Kyung-hwan and Seogy

643.SummaryEnglish:
On today’s episode, Cha Tae Hyun becomes the master, and other members swear their loyalty to become his butler. But as expected, Master Cha does not treat them fairly or has intentions to do so. Unsatisfied butlers do whatever they can to bring him down, but Master Cha is not an easy target. Master Cha’s abuse of power continues as the butlers take one step at a time to end his dictatorship. Will they succeed?

Guests: Cha Tae-hyun and Yoo Yeon-seok

644.SummaryEnglish:
With coins changing hands, Master Cha’s reign continues as the cursed roulette points in his favor. Finally, things are about to shift, and an unexpected member becomes the next master. The members are shocked when they see a banner on the wall that has a shocking message. One of the things Seok Jin promised during the previous episode comes back to haunt him.

Guests: Cha Tae-hyun and Yoo Yeon-seok

645.SummaryEnglish:
Joo Woo Jae and Roh Yoon Seo participate with the members in choosing their mentors for the variety show. Despite their excitement upon entering the lecture room, they are taken aback by the unexpected presence of someone they did not anticipate encountering. With the new generation members showing off their trendy games, the oldies also show what they are capable of as the masters of variety shows.

Guests: Joo Woo-jae and Roh Yoon-seo

646.SummaryEnglish: Excited to try new things and local cuisine in Se Chan's hometown of Dongducheon, the members are mindful of the expenses that come with any trip. With no knowledge of the remaining balance on their accounts, they must manage their spending wisely to avoid maxing out their credit cards and facing penalties for breaking the rules. As tensions rise, the members begin casting suspicious glances at each other, as has often been the case in the past.

647.SummaryEnglish:
The members are always active in keeping up with the latest trends in fashion, music, and clothing, with Haha being singled out by Jae Seok as the most enthusiastic. While in Suncheon, they engage in a game of ttakji to determine who among them will be treated to a lavish lunch. The competition heats up as the staff joins the fray, with the stakes now raised for dinner.
No guests

648.TitleEnglish: Perfect Camping for the Season Part 2
648.SummaryEnglish:
The members need to prepare the dinner for themselves, and as is always the case, the scene becomes a total mess when everyone starts to meddle in. The worst is So Min. She tries to make a soup for everyone, but the soup turns into something that Jae Seok hates the most. After the culinary disaster, they must play ttakji, the outcome of which will determine whether they have a comfortable night's sleep or a chilly one in their tents.

No guests

649.SummaryEnglish:
Guests: Kang Hoon and Shin Ye-eun
It’s been many years since the members started behaving shamelessly on Running Man, but this time, they’ve gone a little too far. Among the beautiful scholars, there is one who doesn’t fit the group. Games are played and hints are traded, all to find the one who doesn’t belong. Unless they single out the outcast, it will only be a matter of time before they get the penalties themselves. Stay tuned!

650.SummaryEnglish: The members and staff waited three years preparing for this meet and greet in the Philippines. Despite their eagerness to express gratitude to their fans, they still have missions to fulfill. Once the missions are completed, the members gather at the venue for rehearsals, their hearts brimming with excitement that's hard to contain.

651.SummaryEnglish: Meeting with Manny Pacquiao, their beloved friend, in the Philippines and sharing a meal at his grand mansion is a rare and special occasion for the group. Knowing that such opportunities do not come by every day, they are thrilled to spend a delightful day with him. However, all great things come at a cost, and the members are surprised by the unexpected challenge of R coins, igniting a race to resolve it.

652.SummaryEnglish: The staff is organizing the Running Tour Project, which is a significant undertaking that will give members the chance to travel to their desired destinations. In a show of generosity, the staff is offering opportunities to earn travel budgets provided the members work cohesively. However, the situation takes a turn for the worse as some members begin to betray their colleagues for personal gain, causing chaos and eroding trust among the team.

653.SummaryEnglish: The members have been split into three teams for a high-stakes race that will determine the future of the TV rating notice's new concept. The victorious team will earn the exclusive opportunity to showcase their idea prominently at the beginning of all upcoming episodes, ensuring their brilliance shines brighter than the rest. The drawing will be divided into seven fragments, and those who retrieve them will have the freedom to revise them as they see fit. And so, the race commences.

654.TitleEnglish: TV Rating Notice Painting Exhibition Part II
654.SummaryEnglish: In this week's episode, the TV Rating Notice theme has been decided through Seven Person Banksy, and the members will dress up according to the chosen drawing. Meanwhile, for poor So-min, who always fails to team up with the guest of her choice, there will be a special episode for her, which is called 2023 So-min's Choice Race. Se-ho and Kang Hoon join the team this week, and So-min gets to choose her teammate through a quiz.

655.SummaryEnglish: In this week's episode, the battle between Team Jeon So-min and Team No So-min continues with Se-ho and Kang Hoon. So-min always has been a ref for sports games, but she finally becomes a top player in 2023 So-min's Choice Race. Stay tuned to check out the impressive moments of So-min and Name Tag Elimination at a huge used car store in Cheongna.

656.SummaryEnglish: Kim Dong-hyun, the friendly family member of Running Man, is here as a guest. Today, he and Se-chan will lead their teams to victory. They will participate in games that need both physical strength and strategic ideas. Depending on the Golden and Fake eggs that they get along the way, the winning and losing teams will be decided.

657.SummaryEnglish: Continuing from a few weeks back, Ji-hyo gets to plan her trip any way she likes, so she sets up the "Detox Tour" for the entire crew where the members have to follow exactly what Ji-hyo says. If anyone resists, they will be punished. Some members enjoy it while others think it's the worst thing

658.SummaryEnglish: In this week's episode, Variety Solos are here at Variety Solo World to find their Variety Mates! With a rising star, Dex, and familiar actresses, Lee Se Hee and Han Ji Eun, joining the show, they create a complicated drama, which no one expected. They have to fight each other to get the votes. Will they be able to find their mates? Stay tuned!

659.SummaryEnglish: In this week's episode, Lucky 29th Race begins with the members choosing their favorite number between 0 to 9. When the race ends, they will pick one number card out of the two numbers, 2 and 9. Three members who have completed or are the coolest to the number will get the golden R coins. Who will be the lucky members with the lucky number? Stay tuned!

660.SummaryEnglish: In this week's race, they have to complete one straight line on a bingo board with a variety of summer noodle dishes. They only get to eat the recommended dishes from citizens to check a slot on the board, and they need at least three different dishes to complete it. Will they be able to get off work just in three attempts?

661.SummaryEnglish: In this week's episode, Joohoney and Yun Sung Bin join the members to have Go Away Age Party at Running Man. They are divided into two teams, Team Jong Kook and Team Sung Bin, to play games. There are various prizes ready for the party, and the team that earns more R coins wins the prizes.

662.SummaryEnglish: The members are invited to the first Running Scout Festival. There will be various limited edition badges, and the members have to collect them through games. They can exchange badges at a store for money. Which one of them will finish this race with a truckload of cash?

663.SummaryEnglish: The seven gamblers from Joseon Dynasty are coming to win a fortune in just one day. With the candies they've earned through the race, they can purchase a talisman that they can use during the final table game. The moment a talisman is activated, the flow of the game will be completely upset. Who will be the best gambler in the country?

664.TitleEnglish: Yoo Jae Seok's Exploration of Cultural Heritage
664.SummaryEnglish: In this week's episode, the members go on the second trip of the Running Tour Project designed by Jae-suk, called Yoo Jae-suk's Exploration of Cultural Heritage. With enthusiastic Professor Yu, they arrive at Gyeongju the day before the shoot to join the tour early next morning. They will have history quizzes throughout the tour and get a Running Ball each time they score. With the Running Balls, they decide on the next trip designer for the Running Tour Project.

665.TitleEnglish: Summer Vacation Special, Running Man Outing
665.SummaryEnglish: In this week's episode, the members will carry out outdoor games and missions at Grandma's house in a village for their summer vacation. After each activity, they will write down a picture journal about things they did well and things they want other members to work on. Based on the vote, they will get the coupons to win the prize of 3 million won.

666.TitleEnglish: Summer Vacation Special, Running Man Outing Part 2
666.SummaryEnglish: The race in the mud continues with Se Chan and Jong Kook. Will Se Chan be able to create a twist against Jong Kook? Meanwhile, there will be a table tennis match that comes with a penalty everyone hates. Which team will need to wake up at the crack of dawn to pick bell peppers and make breakfast next morning?

667.TitleEnglish: Summer Vacation in Fishing Village: Running Man Outing
667.SummaryEnglish: In this week's episode, the members will carry out outdoor games and missions at Grandma's house in a village for their summer vacation. After each activity, they will write down a picture journal about things they did well and things they want other members to work on. Based on the vote, they will get the coupons to win the prize of 3 million won.

668.TitleEnglish: Summer Vacation in Fishing Village: Running Man Outing Part 2
668.SummaryEnglish: This time, the members spend a day at an elderly gentleman's house in the fishing village. From early morning, they harvest sea urchins and make breakfast with them from scratch. In the evening, they play games to pick two unlucky members for the worst penalty.

669.SummaryEnglish: On the last night of Summer Vacation Special, the members have a revenge match of table tennis. This time, they have to play with special rackets that suit the heat of summer. Who will be the loser to go on a fishing boat the next morning? Meanwhile, Detectives on a Summer Night Race begins with a guest, Kang Hoon, joining the members. They have to win hint tickets through missions before they receive a request. They can use their hint tickets to solve the mystery case.

670.SummaryEnglish: The eight great detectives get given two new cases revolving around two mysterious murders. After splitting up into two groups, they face each other in a quest to find the suspects. Which odd pairing will have what it takes to look for evidence, find clues, and earn hints as they battle their fears in a gruesomely horror-filled theme?

671.SummaryEnglish: This week, V of BTS joins the show during his layover as a wealthy landowner with plots of land all over the country. Each region possesses a specialty food that tenant farmers must fight for. However, V makes all the decisions according to each tenant farmer's performance. The one with the most coins wins, and they get a shot at overthrowing V's control. Will V keep all his land and reap the riches?

672.SummaryEnglish: The Running Man members head over to Daehakro for the Money Road in Daehakro Race. At each venue they visit, they will complete a mission where the winner gets to distribute the prize money to the members. However, they can object to the amount they get given and revolt. If that happens, there is a chance more members will get the penalty at the end of the race. Who will escape the punishment?

673.SummaryEnglish: Inherent complexity already surrounds love relationships, but the members aim to discover both the popular and suitable individuals for themselves. However, amnesia stemming from a tragic accident presents a compelling and daunting obstacle. The popular figures remain concealed within the group of nine, initiating a search that promises eventual chaos. Clues offer only vague guidance in narrowing down the potential candidates. Can they ultimately find their genuine soulmates?

674.SummaryEnglish: Yoo Seung Ho, Kim Dong Hwi, and Yu Su Bin will join today's race! They will split up into two teams with the members and make money deals with the production crew led by the Mask Man. However, the money must cascade within the team, so it's all about loyalty and greed. The three with the most money win a prize, and the three with the least amount face the penalty. Which team captain will lead them to victory?

675.SummaryEnglish: Um Ki Joon, Yoon Jong Hoon, and Lee Joon, three survivors of "The Escape of the Seven," join the show in this week's race, The Escape of the Ten. Their objective of the race is to figure out what crime they have committed in order to escape. Through a variety of missions, they have the chance to win coins to buy hints of their sins. The race starts now.

676.SummaryEnglish: Hoshi, Seungkwan, and DK from SEVENTEEN join the cast in this week's Minority's Paradise Race. A big red button will determine their fates in the race. The ratio of those who choose to press it against those who don't will decide if they go to Paradise or to the Inferno. Through a series of missions, they get a chance to win coins that will help them escape facing the punishment in the final round. Who will live in Paradise, and who will suffer in the Inferno? Guests: DK, Hoshi and Seung-kwan (BSS)

677.SummaryEnglish: MIYEON from (G)I-DLE and Mimi from OH MY GIRL are here for this week's Fall Gourmet Party Race! They will enjoy some of the best fall dishes only if they win in the missions. However, after each challenge, they will either collect multiple prize badges or penalty badges that will get drawn at the end, determining their fates. What tasty fall menus will entice their competitive spirit? Guests: Mimi (OH MY GIRL) and Miyeon [(G)I-DLE]

678.TitleEnglish: The Dream of a Million Dollars
678.SummaryEnglish: In this week's episode, a hide-and-seek game worth 1,000 dollars begins. The members have to find the hidden prize envelope with 1,000 dollars. The person whose name is written last on the prize envelope gets the prize money. However, there's a hidden rule that will determine two members who will get the penalty of the day. Who will be able to protect the prize until the end?

679.SummaryEnglish: After seven years, it's the last episode of Running Man for So Min. The cast and crew dedicate this day to So Min and give her the Goodbye So Min Tour, where she gets to do things she likes one last time with the whole cast. However, there are hidden missions that the members must do to get out of the penalty. Watch the heart-rendering moments the cast shares with So Min as they say their goodbyes.

680.TitleEnglish: Do You Want to Win in Singapore?
680.SummaryEnglish:
This week, Running Man races in Singapore! It's the Do You Want to Win in Singapore? race, and there is a luxurious prize on the line. Guests Shin Ye Eun and Hong Jin Ho join the race to lead a team of their own. While picking random cards and keeping their greed at bay, they get to enjoy the best Singapore has to offer. Which team will get the extravagant prize in Singapore?

Guests: Hong Jin-ho and Shin Ye-eun

681.SummaryEnglish: The race in Singapore continues! In teams of two, they will compete in missions where the winning team enjoys the trip for free at the losing team's expense. The team with the most money left will win the race, and the team with the least will face an embarrassing penalty. What fabulous meals and trips will

682.SummaryEnglish: Yoo Seung Ho and V make a return to Running Man, with Seung Ho seeking payback for the previous insults he endured on the show. In this special card shark episode, participants aim to accumulate as many caramels as they can, which play a crucial role in the upcoming challenges. V, armed with sharp wit, successfully takes control of the caramel stash, while Seung Ho struggles with various tasks.

683.SummaryEnglish: It's Se Chan's turn to host a trip for the members, and he plans to throw an early 60th birthday party for Seok Jin. Although the budget isn't as much as he needs, he manages to pull off everything he thinks Seok Jin deserves. From a floral palanquin to a comedy show and his favorite foods, Seok Jin gets showered with adoration. Will Seok Jin enjoy his birthday party?

684.TitleEnglish: Come Empty, Return Empty: The Emptying War
684.SummaryEnglish: Joo Hyun Young, Tsuki, and Kwon Eun Bi are here to race with the cast for as many R coins in a free-for-all, grab-and-dash race! However, there's a catch that the members don't learn about until it's too late. Ironically, less is more, and the people with the most left will face the penalty. But hope is not all lost. They get the chance to discard them by winning missions. Let the Come Empty, Return Empty race begin.

685.SummaryEnglish: In this week's episode, Kim Dong Hyun and TOMORROW X TOGETHER are here for the Christmas Eve Race with Running Man. To get as many presents as possible on Christmas, the members of TOMORROW X TOGETHER are fast asleep in a bedroom. Meanwhile, Dong Hyun and the mischievous members of Running Man have to wake the boys up within ten minutes. Will they be able to get a present for Christmas? Stay tuned!

686.SummaryEnglish: In this week's episode, a crisis falls on the peaceful Running Villa. As the level of disaster keeps increasing, they have to find the bank card with the maintenance fees and repair the house. However, the more they try to repair it, the more problems they run into. Will they be able to overcome the crisis? Stay tuned!

687.SummaryEnglish: In this week's episode, the 2nd Winter Festival takes place to celebrate the new year, and Kyu Hyun, Cho Sae Ho, and Eom Ji Yoon join the members for the fishing tournament! They will play games to acquire the fish traps with different types of bait. The more fish they catch, the higher the chance they'll win a prize. Who will be the winner to take the luxurious prize home? Stay tuned!

688.TitleEnglish: Is This the Table I Like?
688.SummaryEnglish: In this week's episode, the members will travel back to the Joseon Dynasty and find the six dishes for King Seok Sam. Each team has to find three dishes with the names from the Joseon Dynasty on time, and the team members can get prizes if they prepare all three dishes correctly. However, a terrible penalty awaits for those who fail to find the dishes. Will they be able to prepare a royal table for King Seok Sam?

689.SummaryEnglish: After 28 days of rest, Jee Seok Jin is back to join the cast! He receives a warm welcome and a surprise health checkup with all members. Healthy rewards can be theirs, even gold, if they fulfill the health standards that will light up the five smiley faces at the Running Health Center. Will they pass the health checkup and keep their stress levels low and heart rates normal to win the prizes?

690.SummaryEnglish: In this week's episode, the members have the Wonderful Value for Money Race. They visit places where they can have a hearty meal at a reasonable price despite the price hikes. Unlike usual, the three members with the least money left from their mission fund win the race and get amazing prizes. Who will be the winners to spend all they have on a cost-efficient food tour? Stay tuned!

691.SummaryEnglish: To celebrate Lunar New Year's Day, the Jee family gathers to return the favor to those who helped them on the show while Seok Jin was away. They make New Year's food for them and give them a chance to win Lunar New Year presents as well. Who will be the lucky guests to have a delicious meal and get a special gift from the Jee family? Stay tuned!

692.SummaryEnglish: In this week's episode, the members search a mansion for the missing legendary gold bar with Bo Hyun and Ji Hyun. They fight to get crucial clues about the gold bar through debates, interrogations, and games. The member who finds the gold bar will be the sole winner and get the prize today. Who will be the owner of the legendary gold bar?

693.TitleEnglish: I Will Be the Winner in the Next Life
693.SummaryEnglish: In this week's episode, the members and the guests return to the past and live a new life! With the information they have from the future, they get to invest in various fields to increase their assets. However, they have to invest their money wisely as they will be sent to random periods each round. Who will be the winner in the next life? Stay tuned!

694.SummaryEnglish: Team Jae Seok made a successful investment at first, but completely fell to the bottom when they time-traveled to the 2000s. However, they get one last opportunity to rise to the top. Will they be able to turn the table? Meanwhile, the members start school as freshmen for the entering class of 2024, and they compete with one another to earn the scholarship through various campus activities. Stay tuned!

695.TitleEnglish: Star Teacher Yoo Jae Seok's History Trip with the Empty Heads
695.SummaryEnglish: In this week's episode, the seven empty heads go on a history tour with Star Lecturer Yu Jae Seok to learn about Joseon Dynasty. With a matching team uniform, the members set off to Injeongjeon in Changdeokgung Palace. After exploring each spot, Star Lecturer Yu will give history quizzes, and those who give correct answers will receive benefits. However, one member with the fewest points will get a penalty.

696.SummaryEnglish: The members are excited to visit longstanding restaurants that have been operating for generations, yet they are unaware of the extent of their culinary journey. Beginning with a 92-year-old ox-tail soup place, they embark on a gastronomic exploration of historic restaurants, each with a minimum of 30 years of heritage. Thus, the feast commences.

697.SummaryEnglish: With Jae Seok and Jong Kook leading their respective teams, the two sides engage in a competitive futsal match. Because of the limited number of members, both teams are allowed to recruit players externally. Jae Seok's team reaches out to Oh Ha Young from Apink, who initially responds to Haha's call with caution. On the other hand, Jong Kook identifies Kang Hoon as a potential asset for his team and reaches out to him. An intense futsal showdown commences.

698.SummaryEnglish: In Seongsu-dong, members have the opportunity to experience three exciting courses, all by rolling dice to cover the costs. Each member receives six dice. Following each course, members roll their dice in private. They deduct ten dollars for each point rolled from the total cost of the course. If there's still an outstanding balance, it converts into debt. The number of members penalized depends on the amount of debt incurred. Those penalized will have to sport a pantsless look for next week's shoot. Stay tuned!

699.TitleEnglish: Spring Has Come to TV Rating Notice
699.SummaryEnglish: To serve the penalty from last week's race, the members adopted a pantsless theme, wearing outfits with extremely short bottoms. Dressed in these distinctive attires, they participate in a poster shoot for the show, playfully admonishing Jae Seok for his lackluster bottom. Following this, they embark on a mission to navigate a 50km course, pausing at renowned spring food destinations along the route. Stay tuned to discover if they succeed in completing the rating notice shoot.

700.SummaryEnglish: In honor of the 700th episode of the longest-running show Running Man, the cast bands together for challenges to win a prize of 7,000 dollars. Initially united, tensions rise as they face difficult tasks like spinning 360 degrees on a swing and hitting a small target with a dart. Though they conquer challenges as a team, greed surfaces when it's time to share the prize, sparking a race for personal gain.

701.SummaryEnglish: FC Ttuk and FC Kook, led by Manager Ttuk and Manager Kook respectively, are set to clash in the 2nd Futsal Running Cup. Manager Ttuk, fueled by the desire for revenge after their prior defeat, is determined to turn the tables this time around. However, despite recruiting new members for today's game, he finds himself dissatisfied with the lineup he's assembled.

702.TitleEnglish: The Future of Han Na's Day
702.SummaryEnglish: In this episode, the cast prepares for The Future of Han Na's Day race, where they'll compete according to the rules outlined in Han Na's notebook. What started as a mere guide has transformed into a rigid code, pushing the members to search desperately for it, hoping to tweak the instructions in their favor. As revisions pile up, penalties increase, fueling fiercer competition. Meanwhile, Han Na stands firm, determined to safeguard her notebook at all costs.

703.SummaryEnglish: In this episode, Eun Bi makes a bold return to the show despite being banned by the members. She joins the rest of the cast as they head toward Ganghwa Island. The members playfully rib Eun Bi for her audacity in coming back, especially after her history of tricking Jong Kook. Surprisingly, the more they tease her, the more shameless she becomes. Eventually, she even considers filling an empty spot on the show. With Eun Bi seeming to fit in better than some of the original members, the quizzes carry on.

704.SummaryEnglish: Byeon Woo Seok has made a comeback to the show after a two-year absence, but he's feeling let down by Seok Jin's lack of recollection about his previous appearance. Woo Seok also recounts an anecdote about his first encounter with Woo Jae and reflects on his initial impressions. Later on, Woo Seok shines in the games, impressing everyone with his skill and making strategic decisions that pay off in the final race.

705.TitleEnglish: I Have to Come in First Place
705.SummaryEnglish: An Yu Jin and REI from IVE have joined the show and are placed into two different agencies managed by Jong Kook and Jae Seok. Yu Jin joins Jong Kook's agency, while REI joins Jae Seok's. Each agency then proceeds to select two more trainees. When it comes time to choose their songwriters, one agency collaborates with the renowned EZUZ, while the other ends up using an AI songwriting tool. Stay tuned to find out more.

706.SummaryEnglish: Kang Hoon brings his charm to the show as a guest, but his presence hints at something deeper. He's introduced as the very first rented member, yet he doesn't hold back, speaking his mind directly and amusing others with his straightforwardness. Later, he ventures onto the streets incognito, testing if he's recognizable. During this, Jae Seok inquires about his agency, leading to the revelation that it's the same as Ye Eun's. Jae Seok's remark about him taking her place deeply affects Hoon, stirring up emotional turmoil.

707.SummaryEnglish: This week, Ji Ye Eun and Park Ju Hyun join the cast in the Real and Fake Partners race. Among the cast and the two guests, there are two destined partners. The rest are fake partners. The two destined partners must conceal their identities as they partner with the rest of the group to win missions and gain clues to a passcode that unlocks an account to which they can withdraw money to win the race. Who are the destined partners, and can they escape the penalty and win the reward?

708.TitleEnglish: 3rd Hwang Hee-chan Cup Futsal Running Cup
708.SummaryEnglish: It's the third Futsal Running Cup Championships, and it's time for a new champion. This time, Hwang Hee Chan joins FC Ttuk to help Manager Kim overcome the more powerful FC Kook, led by Manager Kook. ZICO, Jang Hyuk, Kang Jae Jun, Heo Kyeong Hwan, and Oh Ha Young join the Running Cup to make it an even match. Will Hwang Hee Chan's involvement turn things around, or will the players of FC Ttuk be too terrible to turn things around?

709.TitleEnglish: 3rd Hwang Hee-chan Cup Futsal Running Cup II
709.SummaryEnglish: Hwang Hee Chan demonstrates his abilities for FC Ttuk, which has been on a losing streak against the formidable FC Kook. However, the players on FC Ttuk have been more disappointing than he anticipated. Hee Chan decides to take matters into his own hands due to their underwhelming performance. Despite his efforts, FC Kook proves to be a tough opponent, eager to extend their winning streak. Meanwhile, Ji Ye Eun returns to the show and reveals her ulterior motive.

710.SummaryEnglish: The youngest member, Kang Hoon, shakes things up by embracing his betrayal DNA. On this Gourmet Vacation, only those who successfully predict the card limit amount get a meal. Kang Hoon, who first wins the right to order, employs a sneaky strategy to limit the other members' meals. He collectively deceives the members, causing an uproar, and then makes shocking confessions with an innocent expression.

711.SummaryEnglish: Ji Ye Eun joins Running Man once again, and she gets to be a captain along with Seok Jin in a race all about options. The Unknown Options Race gives members two options to choose from. One leads them to Seok Jin and the other to Ye Eun. With the teams decided, badges will be given to the captains to allocate among the members. In the end, the more badges give them a higher probability of escaping the penalty. Who knows who better to escape the penalty?

712.SummaryEnglish: Nam Ji Hyun and P.O join today's Good and Bad Partner Race. For the race, paired rival members will choose one of two briefcases containing something good or bad. If it's good, they become the Good Partner. If it's bad, they become the Bad Partner. After verifying what's inside, they will claim they are the Good Partner and try to entice the other members to choose their briefcase for better rewards. Who has what it takes to lie and earn more members for worthy prizes?

713.TitleEnglish: Temperature Differences in the Middle of Summer
713.SummaryEnglish: The members seek vacation destinations to escape the sweltering summer heat. They will be throwing darts at a map of Seoul, divided into 25 regions, to discover unique summer vacation spots recommended by locals. Before the race, the members are assigned to group missions, with the chance to earn benefits if they win. As expected, some members fall short of others' expectations and face ridicule. Thus begins another chaotic day on Running Man.

714.SummaryEnglish: Before the main race begins, the members are assigned a mission. Jae Seok and Jong Kook must each pick up three members in their cars and reach the destination first. However, contrary to expectations, Ye Eun hesitates to get into Jae Seok's car, even with Kang Hoon present. Later, during the main event, Jong Kook gives Ye Eun an opportunity to showcase her athletic skills, which she is very confident about. However, Jong Kook draws a different conclusion.

715.SummaryEnglish: The members visited the landlord’s house for snacks and were shocked to find Yu Chun Ja eliminated. Their final mission was to identify the culprit, leading them to search the house and village for clues. They learned the homeowner had feared someone spying on her and left a will with a neighbor after burying something. Discovering leather pieces with incriminating writings, the members begin suspecting each other.

716.TitleEnglish: Running Summer Games with the National Athletes
716.SummaryEnglish: National athletes who achieved remarkable records in Paris join the group for the Running Summer Games. Fencing champions Sang Uk and Park Sang Won, judo stars Min Jong and Ha Yoon, and weightlifter Hye Jeong captivate the members with their skills and humor. Sang Uk's charisma particularly impresses the regulars, resulting in some amusing interactions with Jae Seok and Jong Kook. The episode features highlights such as a playful poetry and dance challenge and a high jump competition.

717.SummaryEnglish: Today's race is the Happy Dice Race.
