Kim Ah Young and Joo Hyun Young join as guests, representing Gen Z, and they join to celebrate Jae Seok, Haha, and Ji Hyo's birthdays, the seniors. Each of the seniors will get separate birthday parties, where they must win to enjoy their birthday feast. Everyone will also play for badges, and the ones with the fewest badges will get the most annoying penalty.

718.SummaryEnglish: Today, the members visit Jae Seok, Seok Jin, and Ji Hyo's childhood neighborhood, Suyu-dong, in the Lucky Catch in Suyu-ri Race. Finding hidden R Stickers around well-known locations will grant them a childhood gift they've always wanted. Winning missions will give them hints as to where they can locate them. Who will race to find the exchange coupons and win their childhood toy?

719.SummaryEnglish: Keum Sae Rok and Hong Jin Ho join the cast as today's guests in the Unlucky Family is Here Race. Two families of the Unlucky Family gather for one of the biggest national holidays, Chuseok. They battle each other for the unluckiest draws for chances to alter a three-level roulette board that will determine a prize or a penalty. Which family of the Unlucky Family will be unfortunate enough to leave with a gift or lucky enough to be shamed with a penalty?

720.SummaryEnglish: Kwon Eun Bi and Jonathan Yiombi join as guests in today's The Perfect Code Race. Each Running Man member starts with seed money they get from a random QR code they scan at the start of the race. Eun Bi and Jonathan will have different tasks to earn their money. With that seed money, the members and the guests will scan QR codes in missions to make it grow. In the end, they race with QR codes on their backs with questions they must answer to eliminate the other to earn even more money to determine who faces the penalty.

721.SummaryEnglish: Haewon from NMIXX and Kim Dong Jun of ZE:A join the cast for this week's A Retreat With Pirate Roulette Race as guests. The one who makes the pirate pop will get to call it a day and go straight home. Those who fail will stay to face a penalty. Furthermore, they will only get to eat if they can pop the pirate with the amount of knives they collect through missions and games. Who will get to eat and go home early?

722.SummaryEnglish: This week, it's the Boss of the Alley Race! The members are in for a treat only if they are the Alley Boss. They will visit the many famous food alleys in Seoul, and for each alley, they will fight in a game of slap-match to determine the Alley Boss. The Ally Boss will choose what they eat and won't have to pay. They will also pick two members to eat with them. The others will have to cover the costs. At the end of the race, the three members with the least amount of mission funds left will face a penalty.

723.TitleEnglish: Tenacious Dieters to Keep Weight Off
723.SummaryEnglish: This week, the members' willpower gets put to the test. In the Tenacious Dieters to Keep Weight Off Race, they need to beat the scale throughout the day as they take on missions to keep the weight off and maintain their initial weigh-in as a group. If they go over one kilogram, they risk coming in an hour earlier for the shoot. They get four weigh-in chances, and each failure adds an hour to the penalty. Who will keep their appetite in check?

724.SummaryEnglish: Woo Do Hwan and Lee You Mi join the members in the special episode "The Head Family the Pecking Order." In this thrilling race, everyone plays descendants of a prestigious family, choosing roles as kings, nobles, or slaves, but their status can change at any moment. Who will rise and who will fall? Stay tuned to find out!

725.SummaryEnglish: Kim Ah Young, Seo Eun Kwang, and Lee Min Hyuk join this week's I Can't Live Without Money Race. They will split into two teams, and the team with the most points will win money while the other faces a penalty. There will be Money Challenges in each round where they pick random money briefcases with a positive or negative amount. Whether they stop or keep going will be up to them. Mystery briefcases will also be available with a jackpot, a penalty ticket, or a bomb to entice their greed. Who will win this week's race?

726.SummaryEnglish: Hong Kyung, Roh Yoon Seo, and Kim Min Ju are here to promote their new movie, "Hear Me: Our Summer." They get to show off their wits and acting skills against the members in this week's Be Clever to Trust race. Three teams will compete to make a three-digit number using the number each member picks at random. However, the member with the highest holding number of the winning team won't win the prize, and the highest holding number of the losing team will have a higher chance of getting the penalty. Who will sacrifice themselves for the team? And who will deceive to escape the penalty?

727.SummaryEnglish: Kim Dong Jun joins the cast again, along with RAMI and RORA from BABYMONSTER, in this week's Presumptuous Election for Class President Race. Dressed in their high school uniforms, the cast and guests elect a class president, following a specific theme, who then will have the power to designate teams to fight for badges. At the end of the race, the one with the fewest badges and two randomly picked people will face the penalty.

728.SummaryEnglish: A "Decision to Trust" race unfolded, where hearts had to connect based on mutual trust to clock out for the day with Joo Hyun Young as today's quest. The production team reveals that Seok Jin's growing anger stems from distrust among the members and challenges him to control his temper and rebuild trust during the race. Can the members escape the swamp of 15 years of distrust and uphold the "No Betrayal" vow to the end?

729.SummaryEnglish: The cast prepares their passports for a race of trickery. Keywords obtained through missions will determine the theme and destination of the deception. To escape the penalty, they must produce a picture with a theme and destination that people on the streets can guess correctly. Three world destinations will be visited, with only six hours to complete the race. Let's see what locations Running Man Airlines will land.

730.SummaryEnglish: The Wise Odd and Even Choices Race gets underway with guests Kyu Hyun and Dahyun. To celebrate the end of the year, they will have winter-themed courses to choose from that will determine an odd or even number according to the number of members. Making the wrong guess and decision will make them an eligible candidate for the penalty. Let's see how the members do against the cold weather.

731.TitleEnglish: The Invitation Doesn't Go as Planned
731.SummaryEnglish: Running Man prepares for Christmas and the year's end in this week's The Invitation Doesn't Go as Planned Race. An invitation gets sent to the cast for the overnight year-end party with empty schedule slots. They will fill in the slots by completing missions to win a more favorable outcome for the location and lodging arrangements, where a few will get selected to sleep outside in the cold. Where will they go, and who will sleep outside?

732.SummaryEnglish: On today’s episode of Running Man, the cast headed to Gangwon Province for a year-end party that brought plenty of laughs as Ye Eun’s bold outfit and clumsy heels became a target for jokes. Excitement spiked when Jae Seok revealed Kang Hoon’s upcoming appearance, leading to playful teasing about Ye Eun’s reaction and their chemistry.

733.SummaryEnglish: The So Cool Running Man Year-End Party Race continues, and it's time to determine who will have to spend the night out in the cold. As Jong Kook comfortably enjoys his exemption, the cast battles each other to stay warm by winning secret missions. Who will the unfortunate members be to grunt out the night outside?

734.SummaryEnglish: On today's Running Man, under the theme of "Decision to Leave 2024," actor Kang Hoon returns after five months as the cast shares items they want to leave behind from 2024. Haha blames snacks for his weight struggles, Ye Eun jokes about her scale and weight, Jae Seok reminisces about an old belt from the 2000s, and Jong Kook vents about a broken electric bike.

735.SummaryEnglish: It's the Lucky 2025 race, and the cast goes against the ghost leg game to determine their fates. If they land on Snake, they will perform a task to spread the luck of the Year of the Snake. If they land on Pass, they get a comfortable ride to the next mission. Each mission allows them to change their fates by adding extra legs determined by their finishing position. Let's find out who has the most luck!

736.SummaryEnglish: Actor Choi Daniel and long-time friend Actress Jeon So Min join the cast along with Athletes Park Hye Jeong and Kim Ha Yoon in this week's Sorry for Teamkilling Race, a two-team deathmatch with MC Yu, who has the power to determine the penalty takers. According to a vote after each mission, the member with the most votes will get added penalty balloons, in which MC Yu will throw darts to expose the name behind at the end of the race. The penalty is the dreaded cold-water bomb, and the non-penalty takers go home with a nice prize.

737.SummaryEnglish: Celebrating the Lunar New Year, the cast races for cards that spell out "Blue Snake" in either Korean or Chinese while enjoying cost-effective courses of food and merchandise. It's a team race, and they will get chances to exchange cards only if they win missions by guessing the mind-blowingly cheap prices offered at each venue. How low will prices go, and who will go home with a prize?

738.TitleEnglish: The Person Who Laughs in Paradise
738.SummaryEnglish: Lee Seok Hoon, Kyu Hyun, and Park Eun Tae, musical Actors from "The Man Who Laughs," join the cast in this week's The Man Who Laughs in Paradise Race. To emphasize a key line from the play, where the rich enjoy paradise at the suffering of the poor, they will race for tickets to determine their wealth won through missions throughout the race. The number of tickets will allow them to enjoy Paradise or suffer in the Inferno.

739.SummaryEnglish: The cast dresses up as slaves this week, and if they fulfill their master's errands, they can go home early without facing the penalty. However, since the slaves cannot read, they will decipher clues, succeed in missions, and work to arrive at their destination to carry out the errands on time in this history-themed race. Where will their master send them, and will they even get to eat?

740.SummaryEnglish: Rising star Joo Jong Hyuk and Kim Si Eun, the famous number 95 of the "Squid Game," are here as this week's guests for the family lookalike-themed Family in Joy and Sorrow Race. Three family teams of lookalikes will compete in missions to withdraw money from the other families' accounts. The family with the most money at the end of the race will win a prize, and the lowest amount will face a penalty. Who will face the penalty?

741.SummaryEnglish: Last week's tip given by the cast sets the stage for this week's SOS Heavy Cleaning Zone Race at Kim Jong Kook's house! They are off to his house to see if what they said is true and try to find a means of bringing it up to living standards. Luckily, it's not all trash. Surprisingly, it's a treasure trove of goods, and the items will be up for grabs through missions for the members to take home. In return, Jong Kook gets a chance at winning a big prize. Will they succeed in turning his house around?

742.SummaryEnglish: Choi Daniel and Kim Ah Young join the cast in this week's My Perfect Spending Race to try and revive the economy. They get a whopping three thousand dollars to spend as their allowance, which is a first-ever. However, if they don't spend all the money at the location of their missions, it gets added to the penalty balance. The higher their penalty balance, the more members will face the penalty. How much money will they spend?

743.SummaryEnglish: Heo Kyeong Hwan and national short-track speed skating gold medalists Park Ji Won and Jang Sung Woo join the cast in the 2025 Running Cup Championship Race. Sponsorship is key to winning the race, and there are plenty to choose from. However, only some have high-star ratings, and only some provide race perks. The more stars the team collects, the higher the chance to win the race. Which team will get the sponsorship to win?

744.TitleEnglish: Going Up the TV Rating Notice
744.SummaryEnglish: Get ready for a fresh twist on Running Man's TV rating notice for 2025! The cast heads to the mountains to capture a stunning spring view this year, but the journey to the perfect shot won't be as picturesque. Their stamina will wane, their egos will bruise, and tempers will flare as they battle missions to shorten their climb. Struggling in less-than-ideal hiking gear, the members face grueling terrain, pushing their physical and mental limits. Let's see if they make it to the top.

745.SummaryEnglish: Eun Chae and Sakura from LE SSERAFIM join the cast as special guests for The Going Home in Order of Charging Race. The goal? Leave work on time, but there's a catch. Their phones are dead, and the only way to charge them is to win challenges. Making the final call to the boss lets them clock out, and the last team to succeed faces dreaded overtime. With outdated phones, tangled chargers, and high-stakes missions, will the phones power up for them so they can escape the office on time?

746.TitleEnglish: How a Giant Snake Becomes a Dragon
746.SummaryEnglish: This week on Yimugi Becomes a Dragon Race, BTOB's Yuk Seong Jae and WJSN's Kim Ji Yeon join as special guests. Across Seoul, magical pearls of various ranks, sizes, and shapes, lost by nine yimugis, are scattered, waiting to be found. In teams of two, they must track down and collect these pearls to amass the highest magic pearl level and claim victory. But teamwork alone won't be enough. Each person must also secure a pearl for themselves to escape the penalty.

747.SummaryEnglish: The Running Man cast welcomes Choi Daniel to the family as a rented member in this week's Let There Be a New Family Race. The cast scrambles to get the welcome celebrations in order and even gives him a surprise visit. Little does he know a hidden mission in the visit will determine the race's budget and how the race will pan out. What events and hidden missions will Daniel encounter?

748.SummaryEnglish: Ye Eun gets behind the wheel to turn her novice driving skills into expert ones. After a gauntlet of driving lessons thrown by Jae Seok, Jong Kook, and Daniel, her mission is to pick up the other remaining members scattered about the city. Will Ye Eun make it through the journey as she navigates the streets with unrelenting backseat drivers driving her mad? Let's find out!

749.TitleEnglish: Merchant Chronicles: You Have to Earn to Live
749.SummaryEnglish: The Running Man Selling Association gathers for a chance to make a fortune in this week's Merchant Chronicles, You Must Make Money to Survive Race. The production crew has made a request to the association for items they require, and it's up to the members to find them, buy them, and sell them through an auction. They split into two teams, and whichever team makes the most profit will win the prize and gain a higher chance of escaping the penalty. Who will make the most profit?

750.TitleEnglish: A Good Day to be Solo
750.SummaryEnglish: KAI and Kim Ah Young join this week's A Good Day To Be Solo. In honor of Black Day, when singles celebrate with jjajangmyeon, the cast and guests must team up into couples, no matter gender. But staying single is the ultimate mission. Couples rack up penalty badges and edge closer to defeat. Who will dodge the penalties, stay solo, and seize the final prize?

751.TitleEnglish: The More you Shoot, The More you Succeed
751.SummaryEnglish: A buzzworthy investor in Pocheon announces a massive funding opportunity, enticing Running Man startup CEOs to gather to this week's The More you Shoot, The More you Succeed Race in Pocheon. While visiting Korean Heritage sites across Pocheon, they compete for stamps and clues that will give them the edge to entice investments. The two teams that land an investment contract get to go home earlier, while the other teams face the penalty.

752.SummaryEnglish: The long-standing turf war between the Locust Gang and the Tiger Gang is finally ending. Son Ho Jun and Yoo Seung Ho join the cast as special guests in this week's explosive race of Territorial Expansion of Killers. Multiple battlegrounds await, with the victorious gang claiming the spoils of each turf. Meanwhile, the losers must endure harsh penalties. Who will conquer and who will fall?

753.SummaryEnglish: It's May, Family Month, and MIYEON and SOYEON of i-dle join the cast for a playful race packed with secret missions and quick-witted challenges at locations fit for the holidays celebrated in the month. The members and guests who successfully carry out their required actions will get rewarded, while those who fail will face a penalty. Who has the wits and brains to crack the missions and gain the advantage?

754.SummaryEnglish: Lee Seung Hyub of N.Flying and actress Park Ji Hu join the cast at a vibrant amusement park in Chuncheon for the Spring Voting Race. Over three intense rounds, members face different voting methods, each offering unique benefits to the winners. But with every vote, the stakes grow, and those who lose must endure penalty missions. As pressure mounts and the final penalty looms, tensions rise, and strategies clash. Who will survive the race without facing the penalty?

755.SummaryEnglish: This week, the cast goes on a Drawing Road Trip, where Jae Seok's drawings determine their fate. With only five seconds to draw, Jae Seok's drawings must be good enough for random people to guess the location correctly to move on to the next spot. They must reach a total of three destinations by 4 p.m. If they don't complete the mission on time, they will go on the terrifying Gyro Swing ride as a team penalty before they go home. Will they make it?

756.SummaryEnglish: Kim Ah Young is back to stir up the hearts of Se Chan and Daniel in this summer-themed race all about Incheon, Korea's first city to embrace Western culture. Each of the three levels of cards, gold, silver, and bronze, will have five cards, which only contain one, two, and three factual real cards, respectively, that will determine the prize level they can win. Three teams will race to find the real cards to win the prize, while those who get it wrong will face the penalty.

757.SummaryEnglish: This week, the cast hosts the Empty Head Avengers Competition to find out who's the smartest and the most clueless among Song Ji Hyo, Yang Se Chan, Choi Daniel, and Ji Ye Eun. Meanwhile, the remaining four Brainiacs will place bets using special summer-themed betting money. It's a fierce contest within teams, where every point counts. Only the top scorers will boost their odds of escaping the final penalty. How will the Empty Heads rank?

758.SummaryEnglish: This week's Miracle Breakfast Morning Race catches the cast by surprise. It's a game of bingo with the dishes they said they wanted to eat, but the only way to cross one out is if a random person says that's the dish they want for breakfast. If they cross out three in a row within the set time limit, they get to go home early. If they fail, they face the penalty. Let's see who has the stomach to take on a massive breakfast feast.

759.SummaryEnglish: Asa and Ahyeon of BABYMONSTER, along with Joo Hyun Young, join the cast in this week's Creepy Vacation Thriller Race. In this upgraded three-horror-themed getaway course, members must choose to bravely volunteer for each course or leave their fate to chance by drawing a black or gold ball, leading to either prize balls or penalty balls. Tension runs high, but will they muster the courage to step forward, or leave it up to luck in this chilling summer race?

760.SummaryEnglish: Running Man marks its 15th anniversary with a special guest appearance by SUPER JUNIOR, who are also celebrating 20 years! In this week's You Could Win Gold Today race, everything revolves around collecting R coins. The more they earn, the higher their chances of winning Running Man's ultimate prize, gold. But with fewer coins, the risk of facing a harsh penalty rises. What outrageous games await in this chaotic and unforgettable anniversary celebration?

761.SummaryEnglish: MIYEON joins the cast in the stunning historic city of Gyeongju for this week's Splitting Gamblers Race, which was inspired by the region's unique seashell artifacts. Each member selects one shell they believe will be the hardest to break among the many on display. In the final showdown, they'll try to smash each other's shells, while hoping theirs don't break. The last player with their shell intact wins the prize, while the rest earn penalty balls in the draw. Who will outlast the shell-cracking chaos?

762.SummaryEnglish: The cast arrives at Ye Eun's stunning new home, ready to celebrate her birthday with carefully chosen gifts. But their offerings must pass the ultimate test from the picky new homeowner, who values her aesthetic above all else. Some friendships might not survive the vibe check.

763.SummaryEnglish: Nam Woo Hyun, Kim Ha Neul, and Lee Jun Young join the cast for this week's Roulette Battle of Weak Loyalty Race, where unexpected alliances take center stage. A large roulette wheel with 60 empty slots will slowly fill through missions and games with their names. They will spin the roulette wheel at the end to determine which three members will get the prize or the penalty. However, if it lands on an empty slot, all members suffer the penalty. Who will walk away with the reward, and who will fall victim to the roulette of fate?

764.SummaryEnglish: The cast sets off on the 2025 Day Goblin's Tour, but this vacation is all about winning R coins! Starting with seed money, members choose from a variety of themed travel rooms, each with its own entrance fee and challenges. Inside, they'll take on games and missions, risking their coins for the chance to earn more. In the end, they'll use their winnings to buy a souvenir, while those who can't afford one will face the penalty. Who will spend smart and who will go broke?

765.SummaryEnglish: Seo Jang Hoon, Shin Gi Ru, and Shindong join the cast for this week's Between Masterpiece and Failure Race. Two rival artist families, the Kims led by Jong Kook and the Yus led by Jae Seok, go head-to-head in a drawing showdown to see who can create the most valuable masterpiece. AI will evaluate each work by assigning a price to determine its worth. The winning family claims prizes, while the losers face the penalty. Which family of artists will reign supreme?

766.SummaryEnglish: This week, the Running Sports University Prize Battle Race gets underway with world champion judo siblings Kim Min Jong and Kim Ha Yoon as guests. Before each training session begins, members compete in games to earn Running Balls, which can be placed into raffle boxes. When a box exceeds ten balls, a raffle is drawn for prizes. Winners gain immunity from the penalty, while those left without prizes face imminent doom. The games are tense and the prizes grand. Who will have the luck to win!

767.TitleEnglish: The More you Spend, The More Luck you Get! Date Bursting with Luck.
767.SummaryEnglish: This week, Kim Ah Young and Jang Dong Yoon join the cast for the "Spend More, Get Lucky. Jackpot Date." Inspired by the Sangsaeng Consumption Lottery, the cast pairs up for a special spending race where every purchase over a set amount earns them a lottery ticket. Along the way, games and missions allow them to earn extra Running Money, which determines their order of spending on a date. At the end, the three members with the highest totals will win prizes, while three unlucky random players face penalties. Who will strike it rich, and who will pay the price?

768.TitleEnglish: Time Attack, Prize and Penalty Fighter
768.SummaryEnglish: The cast kicks off with a 20-minute challenge right off the bat. Gather in one area by using a walkie-talkie with only a 300m range, or risk being added to the penalty list every time each member misses the mark. The reward? An early finish with only prizes in hand. Once together, they dive into the Time Attack Win, Lose Fighter Race, where every second counts. If all tasks are cleared by four, prizes await. Will the members push through to earn an early escape, or fall victim to penalties?

769.SummaryEnglish: This week's race is Go Straight with Your Answer! Based on the questionnaires the cast fills out earlier, the answers will get randomly pieced together into a complete sentence that will decide today's missions. Ranging from destinations to activities, everything gets determined by chance, and the stakes are high. If they can't complete the mission by 3 p.m., everyone will face a massive team penalty. Will the cast have answers that will lead them to triumph, or send them on a chaotic detour to disaster?

770.SummaryEnglish: Jong Kook's best friend, Cha Tae Hyun, joins us for this week's Congratulatory Delegation with Kook's Patience race to celebrate Jong Kook's wedding. But for someone who cringes at even a birthday song, today's over-the-top party is pure torture. Through missions, the members will try to remove corny and fussy celebration items, while Jong Kook collects chance cards to his advantage. Every chance card he uses adds another penalty member. Will Jong Kook endure the embarrassment, or will the celebration spiral out of control?

771.TitleEnglish: Sir, That Salary Goes to the CEO
771.SummaryEnglish: This week, Kwon Eun Bi and Joohoney join the cast in the Dear CEO, Give Me the Salary Race. Members join companies where they think they'll thrive. However, CEOs will split the profits as salaries as they see fit without the employees knowing. If employees suspect their CEO is embezzling money, they can report them to the Ministry of Labor, but risk losing if their CEO is innocent. The top five salaries win prizes, while the rest face penalties. Which CEO will be the most trustworthy?

772.SummaryEnglish: Guests Jun Hyun Moo and Jung Seung Hwan join in celebration of Chuseok, where two rival lords, Yu Jae Seok and Haha, lead their teams in the Lords' Crops Race. Each team must harvest and trade crops to increase their total value, with only the lords and top-ranking slaves earning prizes and immunity from the penalty. However, the slaves can secretly use their saved earnings to overthrow their lord and change the hierarchy and the outcome. Will Jae Seok and Haha have what it takes to stay noble without being overthrown?

773.TitleEnglish: A World Where Only the Average Survive
773.SummaryEnglish: The cast of "Run to the West" joins Running Man for a special race titled A World Where Only the Average Survives. In this unconventional competition, excelling or failing is equally dangerous. Only those who land squarely in the middle can win. Members get split into two balanced teams, and each mission will test their ability to stay perfectly average. The third-place finisher on each team claims the prize, while everyone else risks facing the penalty. Can they resist their competitive instincts and master the art of mediocrity?
